Then they fled into Cales, Where lie they must and will

For sear lest they should meet again With our Angel Gabriel.

We had within our English ship But only three men slain,

And five men burt, the which I hope Will soon be well again.

At Bristol we were landed, And let us praise God still,

That thus hath blest our lusty hearts And our Angel Gabriel.
